[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering dynamic module layers**\n\nThe user wants to know if I could create a dynamic module layer from compiled classes instead of jars. There's a concern about the CodeSource of classes being a problem, especially since native implementation may not support running Java code. While it might run, the code source could be null. I wonder if attempting to define a layer with empty parameters could help detect unsupported scenarios. Let's explore this further!\n\n**Evaluating library metadata**\n\nI'm considering whether the library should exclude the test-specific StringBuilder. Actually, the user could register the method constructor on StringBuilder since it's part of the public API. However, metadata can't encompass everything. Tests might need a generated agent configuration, especially with a native image. It seems like metadata should be limited to internal reflective self-load. Adding it might be okay, especially with the metadata directory being untracked. I’ll check whether the index is tracked.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_03792c65327f0c5d0169f724de0144819f8f9f3ed3b7739bdf\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9yT1Pa3tGdcJhH4wvDY0UKd7M0gDwmq62Czy5WNDrlOfuIrPrhZ6rwbAC2PG_Eg099q1WdBE0Jt1dS1JeNBqWjq5FXESaB38yU93KF0BrC6XS-nDvCbzKpRMfhH0WvJCrAcOdmlK1ATAleUtFAxRbIkP1j_s4MM3WVadpbIxXkJOGEUgu_5d9qGbXFstuFOaUvGepHsqYVe1FYKfrPAqk4HW5R_foMXRiLnmvPGV1A32VnBFWx4DonqzMkkdiZ4_2Ex5Ulzm00jxcMNCaI1CwQo7Y_ReimMBnMNxaHebmbCoHTy6j_XXj16f9HeBwwWxEwHmhdsfzEwWXQ6RkSNQv0DRG6FrNb-ltxQwjD2oXuDJhMKZpa-ZljGYYqBRWhrtqro0mJ2JJ7azczmJrkzHkjLsEzmpmCds0iczHwIYEdAz0Sg-vspetrq9_Um_q7pLvJHxgrQm5vzZXerp_ugnNokUPo3K7fEx1aTZPrXX5dy6LOwZyjlq4RSIDmcju_4bZoX2sLy4XDGKbC3EqgVd8EYXBof-zQZ5q1_YisQQCydj2q1EgmQbXM3EJEC4SEvuMMrFKFrfXcoiq73Mi6v4unEOBv9Zu1J559QL93u3p4ndOGfyX-MTsWdLJNF5S9x49a4NXGc1y4a-nXUIa9cHeYlWHFwMdbdNVm-Qy1or8SEoZYF0ktfmTZ_jJzOMU5g0_KCicrwBBUK4A5MKTE9e